<font color="#FF0000">FEELING GUILT </font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec 27  0:11:08 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Guilt is what you have when you did something wrong.<br>
Not going to Vietnam was not wrong.It was a choice<br>
that people made for many reasons. <br><br>
I for one do not feel guilty for deciding to fight against<br>
the war here at home. I feel sad for those who died<br>
or came home less than whole. <br><br>
We all make choices based on the information we have at<br>
the time. &quot;If only I knew then what I know now&quot;!!<br>
Too bad we didn't. <br><br>
To those who went and feel guilty and to those who did<br>
not go and feel guilty... There is something wrong<br>
with this picture. You all did the best you could with what<br>
you knew at the time. Let there be peace in your hearts<br>
and comfort in your mind. Lets look forward, not back.<br><br>
Your brother,<br><br>
Jed
